<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 27 at 7:42AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Patchy Dense Fog in the Helena Valley...
Patchy dense fog has developed in the Helena Valley this morning.
Visibility will be reduced to a half mile or less at times in the
fog. Exercise caution if driving this morning in the Helena Valley
and be prepared to slow down if visibility is reduced. Given below
freezing temperatures, elevated surfaces such as bridges may
become slick where fog is locally dense. Fog will slowly diminish
through the morning.</description>
